<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002229.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">BigDaddy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Since trolls have naturally high strength and stamina I didn't put any points into them. Instead I put everything into agi and dex. But I have heard rumors that agi and dex hardly make any difference at all. <P>Would I have been better off pumping everything into stamina? <P>Advice on stats in general for a warrior?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Thrud Gutchewer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I did the same with my troll... Im more than happy... I get alot of crits. I get hit alot but not that much  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif">... Id do it.. <P>Thrud</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">TEW</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Dis is what i did<P>Str:120(+1point)<BR>sta:119(+0point)<BR>agi:93(+5points)<BR>dex:93(+19points)<P>Me seem to be oks, im not the greatest warrior out there but i can do my share of 'medicore' damage and usually have enough hps to walk away<P>Nuglug Fuglee<BR>Troll Warrior lvl39 of povar<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">stoneroot</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">My troll warrior has the following stats<P>str 130  (+12)<BR>sta 120  (+1)<BR>agil 90   (+2)<BR>dex 85    (+10)<P>Strength is supposed to increase damage.  Even if its 1 point of damage for every 20 strength its worth it.<P>Stamina affects hp and how long you can swing a weapon.  (I personally believe the second part of stamina is broken)<P>Agility effects ac.  At lvl 50 its about 1 ac for every 3 agil.  <P>Dexterity effects procs.  Critical hits and cripling hits are also supposed to be effected by dexterity.  <P>I made my character with the hopes of eventually getting a soul leech.  Wont happen now but maybe something else will be implemented with a great proc.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">BigDaddy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Great! Thanks for the replies!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Caper</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I've seen on this forum that statistical parsing analysis has shown that STR adds nothing to damage.  The only thing it's good for is increased carrying capacity.  <P>I've seen that the rule for agility over 75 is +6 Agility = +1 AC.  <P>Dex seems to be mostly an investment for the future when you get proccing weapons.  <P>Stamina increases hit points...I don't know the formula, though. Does anyone?<P>If I were playing a Troll I'd be mightily tempted to raise agility to a good break-point for low levels and jack up the stamina for every level.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Rani</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well on my 50 ogre warrior i put 10 points into strength, and boy do i wish i hadnt done that today. <P>If i were to redo a warrior from scratch i would choose troll warrior for the regen and dump ALL points into stamina. Trolls already have nice agility, so if you dont like the stamina idea i suggest you spend more on dex instead then(although this supposedly only helps you get more procs and learn some weapon skills faster).<P>Just my 2 cents</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Guzrud</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I put all but two points into STR, the remaining two went into Agility. If I had it all to do over, I may  have put more into stam and less into str, but items have corrected  my mistakes and now I am fairly happy with my current statline: str 229, stam 153, agi 100, dex 135<P>Guzrud Eyegouger<BR>lvl 50 troll warrior</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
